    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Important form of classical Japanese dance drama that has been performed since the 14th century. It is often based on stories from traditional literature with a supernatural being transformed into human form as a hero telling a story. Noh integrates masks, costumes and various props into a dance-based performance, Emotions are mainly conveyed through stylized conventional gestures.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
